<br>
With the alt-advancement runspeed option for raw jboot speed, I just don't see the need for ever owning a horse (unless I trip over a bag with about 500k plat in it). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uvallshadowstrife.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vall Shadowstrife</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/11/02 5:26:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1087.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I checked the vendors to see ..</span><hr size=1> If I ever get my own guild assembled, I'd buy a horse, as leader. Why? It's a symbol of status, pure and simple. It shows that you're somebody, a powerful person with a ton of cash.  <p>Vall Shadowstrife <BR>
Tier'Dal Scout of Luclin <BR>
Agent of The Ring</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=enheduanna>Enheduanna</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/11/02 6:23:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1087.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I checked the vendors to see ..</span><hr size=1> I completely agree with Vall. Horses are (as in RL) status symbols. I'd love to have one, but doubt I ever will.<br>
<br>
