<br>
I'll try to remember to check next time I'm there, but that won't be for several days. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umheddik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mheddik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 89<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/11/02 7:12:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1087.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Yes</span><hr size=1> Horses are tradeable. Vendors also say they will buy tme. However, they also say that about other formerly nodrop things too, but when you go to sell, they then say they aren't interested. One would have to sell horse to vendor to answer that question, and I don't want to lose 10 percent of the cost of the horse if they buy it. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
